properties.headline: Gale Watch issued January 14 at 6:16PM EST until January 17 at 7:00AM EST by NWS Mount Holly NJ
properties.description:
* WHAT...For the Dense Fog Advisory tonight, dense fog will
reduce visibility to one quarter to one half mile. For the Gale
Watch, northwest winds 25 to 35 kt with gusts up to 45 kt and
seas 3 to 6 feet possible.

* WHERE...Portions of Atlantic coastal waters and Delaware Bay
Waters.

* WHEN...For the Dense Fog Advisory, until 6 AM EST Wednesday.
For the Gale Watch, from Thursday morning through Friday
morning.

* IMPACTS...Strong winds can cause hazardous seas which could
capsize or damage vessels and reduce visibility. Low
visibility will make navigation difficult.
properties.instruction:
Mariners should consider altering plans to avoid possible
hazardous conditions.  Remain in port, seek safe harbor, alter
course, and/or secure the vessel for severe wind and seas.

If you must navigate, proceed with caution. Use proper fog
signals. Make sure all running lights are on. Remember to use
your radar and compass.
